---
import Layout from "../layouts/layout.astro";

const shipCards = [
  {
    label: "VESSEL\nPROFILE",
    title: "USS Kepler",
    body: "Mission history, command structure, deployment record, and the role of Kepler within the Frontier Initiative.",
    href: "/archive/uss-kepler",
  },
  {
    label: "SAGAN\nCLASS",
    title: "Renaissance Three",
    body: "The post-Frontier Day design philosophy that produced the Sagan, Stargazer, and Hathaway classes.",
    href: "/archive/sagan-class",
  },
  {
    label: "SERVICE\nDOCTRINE",
    title: "Distributed Presence",
    body: "Why Starfleet shifted toward resilience, regional support, and sustained engagement across Federation space.",
    href: "/archive/distributed-presence",
  },
];

const railItems = [
  ["Registry", "NCC-83639"],
  ["Class", "Sagan-class Cruiser"],
  ["Commissioned", "2403"],
  ["Length", "540.7 meters"],
  ["Decks", "16"],
  ["Crew", "500"],
  ["Assignment", "Frontier Initiative"],
  ["Status", "Active"],
];
---

<Layout title="Ship" current="ship">
  <main class="interior-shell">
    <section class="page-hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">Section Overview</p>
      <h1>Ship</h1>
      <p class="dek">
        A Sagan-class cruiser assigned to the Frontier Initiative, dedicated to strengthening the connections that bind the Federation together.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="content-layout">
      <article class="main-content">
        <section class="prose-block">
          <h2>USS Kepler</h2>
          <p>
            Commissioned in 2403, USS Kepler is a Sagan-class cruiser assigned to the
            Frontier Initiative. While fully capable of traditional exploration,
            scientific, and diplomatic operations, the vessel's primary mission is the
            maintenance of Federation cohesion across frontier regions, developing
            member worlds, and isolated communities.
          </p>
          <p>
            Kepler functions as a mobile platform for scientists, engineers,
            educators, medical specialists, cultural experts, and Starfleet officers
            working together to ensure that no member world is forgotten.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="prose-block">
          <h2>Why the Sagan Class?</h2>
          <p>
            The Sagan class emerged during a period of reflection within Starfleet.
            Its four-nacelle architecture, extensive internal volume, emergency
            accommodation capacity, and mission flexibility made it uniquely suited
            for long-duration regional assignments far from major fleet support.
          </p>
          <p>
            Rather than serving as a vessel of conquest or deterrence, Kepler was
            selected because its design aligns with the Frontier Initiative's focus on
            resilience, service, adaptability, and sustained presence.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="prose-block">
          <h2>Variable Mission Craft Facility</h2>
          <p>
            Among the vessel's most distinctive systems is the Variable Mission Craft
            Facility (VMCF), an advanced fabrication and logistics platform capable of
            producing mission-specific shuttlecraft and support vehicles.
          </p>
          <p>
            Known informally by the crew as the "Shuttle Printer," the VMCF allows
            Kepler to construct specialized craft tailored to local conditions rather
            than relying exclusively on a fixed inventory. Survey platforms, medical
            evacuation vehicles, engineering support craft, and environmental response
            shuttles can all be produced as mission requirements evolve.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="prose-block">
          <h2>Technical Specifications</h2>
          <div class="spec-grid">
            <div><strong>Length</strong><span>540.7 meters</span></div>
            <div><strong>Beam</strong><span>195 meters</span></div>
            <div><strong>Height</strong><span>90 meters</span></div>
            <div><strong>Decks</strong><span>16</span></div>
            <div><strong>Crew Complement</strong><span>500</span></div>
            <div><strong>Emergency Capacity</strong><span>3,000</span></div>
            <div><strong>Cruise Warp</strong><span>8.0</span></div>
            <div><strong>Sustainable Warp</strong><span>9.5</span></div>
            <div><strong>Maximum Warp</strong><span>9.9</span></div>
            <div><strong>Shuttlecraft</strong><span>20 Shuttles, 6 Runabouts</span></div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="prose-block">
          <h2>Master Systems Display</h2>
          <img class="msd-image" src="/kepler-msd.png" alt="USS Kepler Master Systems Display" />
          <p>
            The Master Systems Display provides a deck-by-deck overview of the vessel,
            including propulsion systems, major facilities, structural components, and
            mission-critical infrastructure.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="ship-grid">
          {shipCards.map((card) => (
            <a class="ship-card" href={card.href}>
              <p class="card-label">{card.label}</p>
              <h2>{card.title}</h2>
              <p>{card.body}</p>
              <span class="card-action">Open Record</span>
            </a>
          ))}
        </section>

        <section class="prose-block section-note">
          <h2>The Kepler Difference</h2>
          <p>
            Most Starfleet vessels are designed to explore new worlds. Kepler exists
            to strengthen the relationships between worlds already connected by the
            Federation. Its mission is not expansion. Its mission is belonging.
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>

      <aside class="context-rail">
        <section class="rail-card">
          <p class="rail-kicker">Ship Record</p>
          <h2>USS Kepler</h2>
          <p>
            The Ship section documents the vessel, its technical systems, mission adaptations, class lineage, and operational role within the Frontier Initiative.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rail-card metadata-card">
          <h2>Archive Details</h2>
          <dl>
            {railItems.map(([term, detail]) => (
              <div>
                <dt>{term}</dt>
                <dd>{detail}</dd>
              </div>
            ))}
          </dl>
        </section>

        <section class="rail-card related-card">
          <h2>Related Records</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/mission">Mission Framework</a></li>
            <li><a href="/crew">Crew Directory</a></li>
            <li><a href="/logs">Operational Logs</a></li>
            <li><a href="/frontier">Frontier Initiative</a></li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </main>

  <style>
  .spec-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .spec-grid div {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
  }

  .spec-grid strong {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .msd-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
  }
  </style>
</Layout>